description: 3 + 1 Reasons Why This Is The Best RFID Blocking Protection Card For You!
·Easy To Use:
You don’t need to have a degree in mechanics in order to use our card; you simply place your credit/debit cards near it, and you’re done!
·Slim & Compact:
The fact that it has the same exact size as your credit cards, with a thickness of just 0.90 mm, makes it extremely versatile; you can put it in your wallet, your cardholder, or even your pocket!
·No Need For Batteries & Chargers:

You don’t need to worry about needing extra equipment. Our card will use its own “enemy” as a power supply! As soon as the blocking card “encounters” a scanner in your surroundings, it draws energy from it, in order to create a powerful electronic field, making any 13.56 Mhz cards invisible to scanners!
·Superior Quality:
We make a point of using only the best quality materials for our RFID/NFC Signal Protection cards!

OUR RFID / NFC BLOCKING CARD OFFERS 100% PROTECTION FOR BANK CARDS, DRIVER’S LICENCES AND PASSPORTS ONLY, BECAUSE THEY ALL OPERATE ON A FREQUENCY OF 13.56 MHZ. MOST INSTITUTIONAL ACCESS CARDS AND DEVICES OPERATE ON OTHER FREQUENCIES, SO OUR RFID CARD CANNOT PROTECT THEM. Test it yourself!

The easiest way is at a checkout at regular supermarkets. When you have to pay, place our RFID Blocking Card on top (or bottom) of your payment card and approach it to the contactless reader. You’ll notice that your payment card will seem invisible to the reader, or you will get an error message.

Instructions of use
#This is capacitive stylus, so you can use it just like use a pen. The disc tips will help you draw and write more accuracy. (Please do not damage the disc tips, must keep it clean and well)
When you use this pen for different Apps or devices, some of them need to switch to drawing mode or switch to hand writing mode. For example, when you use this pen in Apple Notes App,
you will need to click the small pen writing icon, and then you can make drawing or writing.
#How to change the disc tip
If you want to change the disc, new disc is on the other side that covered by the sliver cap, please screw off the cap and you will see the disc tip.
To replace the disc tip, please pull it out by holding the middle part of the small metal bar, then push a new disc tip into the stylus.
*Use caution
1, Do not pull or cut the disc tip.
2, Can not expose the pen to the sun or close to fire.
3, If the disc tip is worn, please replace the disc tip as soon as possible.
*Common use problem solving
1, When you use this stylus, please let the disc fully touch the screen.
2, If you can not write smooth on the device, the reason would maybe the device is not running enough, please restart the device or turn off other apps.
3, There are dust or grease cover the disc tip, please keep the disc tip clean and well.
4, You can slide the screen, but can not write in the software, please check the software settings or confirm whether the software supports handwriting editing.

Tab and Go

description: Product Description
